# PowerLogger

A high-performance, thread-safe logging library built with Python's logging module and enhanced with the Rich library for beautiful console output with full UTF-8 support.

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/powerlogger.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/powerlogger)
[![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/powerlogger.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/powerlogger/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/powerlogger.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

## âœ¨ Features

- **ğŸ¨ Rich Console Output**: Beautiful, colored logging with the Rich library
- **ğŸ”„ Thread-Safe Queue Logging**: Asynchronous, non-blocking log processing
- **ğŸ“ File Rotation**: Automatic log file rotation with size-based truncation
- **ğŸŒ UTF-8 Support**: Full Unicode and emoji support in log files
- **âš™ï¸ Configuration Management**: Flexible configuration via `log_config.ini`
- **ğŸªŸ Windows Optimized**: Special handling for Windows file access issues
- **ğŸ”§ Multiple Logger Types**: Console-only, file-only, queue-based, and combined loggers
- **âš¡ High Performance**: Optimized for real-time logging applications
- **ğŸ›¡ï¸ Production Ready**: Comprehensive error handling and recovery mechanisms

## ğŸš€ Installation

```bash
pip install powerlogger
```

## ğŸ¯ Quick Start

```python
from powerlogger import get_logger

# Create a basic logger
logger = get_logger("my_app")

# Log messages with beautiful formatting
logger.info("ğŸš€ Application started successfully!")
logger.warning("âš ï¸  This is a warning message")
logger.error("âŒ An error occurred during execution")
logger.debug("ğŸ” Debug information for developers")
```

